This means that we can show \(\color{#BF616A}{TSS} = \color{#8FBCBB}{ESS} + \color{#D08770}{RSS}\)
Step 01: Plug \(y_{i} = \hat{y}_{i} + \hat{u}_{i}\) into TSS
\[\begin{align*}
    \color{#BF616A}{TSS} &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n} (\hat{y}_{i} - \bar{y})^{2} \\
    &= \sum_{i=1}^{n} ([\hat{y}_{i} + \hat{u}_{i}] - [\bar{\hat{y}} + \bar{\hat{u}}])^{2}
\end{align*}\]

This means that we can show \(\color{#BF616A}{TSS} = \color{#8FBCBB}{ESS} + \color{#D08770}{RSS}\)
Step 01: Plug \(y_{i} = \hat{y}_{i} + \hat{u}_{i}\) into TSS
\[\begin{align*}
    \color{#BF616A}{TSS} &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n} (\hat{y}_{i} - \bar{y})^{2} \\
    &= \sum_{i=1}^{n} ([\hat{y}_{i} + \hat{u}_{i}] - [\bar{\hat{y}} + \bar{\hat{u}}])^{2}
\end{align*}\]

Let‚Äôs take a moment to talk about the variance of the OLS estimator

\[
    Var(\hat{\beta}_{1}) = \dfrac{
        \sigma^{2}
        }{
        \sum (x_{i} - \bar{x})^{2}
        }
\]

OLS & Calculus
The calculus we‚Äôll use is by finding the derivatives of the function with respect to \(\hat{\beta}_{0}\) and \(\hat{\beta}_{1}\).
It‚Äôs a lot of algebra but it is simple math, just a lot of it:

\[\begin{align*}
    \min_{\hat{\beta}_{0}, \hat{\beta}_{1}} &\;
    \sum_{i} y_{i}^{2} - \hat{\beta}_{0}y_{i} - \hat{\beta}_{1}x_{i}y_{i} - \hat{\beta}_{0}y_{i} + \hat{\beta}_{0}^{2} + \hat{\beta}_{0}\hat{\beta}_{1}x_{i} - \hat{\beta}_{1}x_{i}y_{i} + \hat{\beta}_{0}\hat{\beta}_{1}x_{i} + \hat{\beta}_{1}^{2}x_{i}^{2} \\
    \min_{\hat{\beta}_{0}, \hat{\beta}_{1}} &\;
    \sum_{i} y_{i}^{2} - 2 \hat{\beta}_{0}y_{i} + \hat{\beta}_{0}^{2} - 2 \hat{\beta}_{1}x_{i}y_{i} + 2\hat{\beta}_{0}\hat{\beta}_{1}x_{i} + \hat{\beta}_{1}^{2}x_{i}^{2}
\end{align*}\]

Then, we take partial derivatives over our choices \(\hat{\beta}_{0}\) and \(\hat{\beta}_{1}\) to figure the best choices.
These are called First Order Conditions (FOCs)

OLS Formulas

Intercept
\[
    \hat{\beta}_{0} = \bar{y} - \hat{\beta}_{1}\bar{x}
\]

Slope Coefficient
\[
    \hat{\beta}_{1} =
    \dfrac{
        \sum_{i=1}^{n} (y_{i} - \bar{y})(x_{i} - \bar{x})
    }{
        \sum_{i=1}^{n} (x_{i} - \bar{x})^{2}
    }
\]
These may look slightly different to my derivation. Part of your assignments is to bridge the gap.

